Verdant green mountains in Arashiyama, south of the Katsura River. So green, I had to turn down the color saturation to make it believable.😉
</p>
<p class="jp">
桂川の南側にある嵐山の、青々とした緑の山々。あまりにも緑が鮮やかだったので、信じてもらえるように彩度を下げざるを得なかった。😉
</p>]]></content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Arashiyama" /><category term="Togetsu Bridge" /><category term="Panoramas" /><summary type="html"><![CDATA[Verdant green mountains in Arashiyama, south of the Katsura River. So green, I had to turn down the color saturation to make it believable.😉 桂川の南側にある嵐山の、青々とした緑の山々。あまりにも緑が鮮やかだったので、信じてもらえるように彩度を下げざるを得なかった。😉]]></summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2713-Pano.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2026/2605_DSC_2713-Pano.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Enjoying the Day・一日を楽しむ</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260505/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Enjoying the Day・一日を楽しむ" /><published>2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2026-05-05T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/arashiyama</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/260505/"><![CDATA[<p class="en">
